<HEADLINE>
<P>
LATE SURGE BY 'ENDING IN PEGASUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Silver Ending made his move on the final turn, took the lead in midstretch and 
scored a two-length victory over another Southland-based colt, Music 
Prospector, in the $300,000 Pegasus Handicap for 3-year-olds at the Meadowlands 
Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
The victory ended a four-race losing streak for Silver Ending, who finished 
fifth in the Kentucky Derby. 
</P>
<P>
He covered the 1 1/8 miles in 1:47 1/5 in winning for the third time in eight 
starts this year and for the fifth time in 13 outings. 
</P>
<P>
The time was three-fifths of a second off the stakes and track record set by 
World Appeal in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye, Silver Ending paid $6.40, $4.40 and $3.40 and 
earned $180,000 for owners Deborah McAnally and Angelo Costanza. The colt has 
earned $914,400. 
</P>
<P>
Longshot Senator To Be led the field through the first three quarters of a mile 
in 1:09 3/5. As the leaders entered the stretch, Senator To Be was a length in 
front of Runaway Stream with Silver Ending, who had been in fifth on the 
backstretch, closing with a rush on the outside. 
</P>
<P>
Silver Ending carried top weight of 119 pounds, three more than Music 
Prospector and eight more than Runaway Stream. Music Prospector paid $13 and 
$7.80; Runaway Stream returned $7.40. 
</P>
<P>
Potentiality broke a close fifth out of the gate, then took the lead after the 
first quarter en route to a 1 1/2-length victory in Friday's $100,000 Island 
Whirl Handicap at Louisiana Downs in Bossier City. 
</P>
<P>
The 4-year-old colt, ridden by Earlie Fires, covered the seven furlongs in a 
near-record 1:22.2 and paid $22.40, $5.80 and $3.80. Favored Black Tie Affair 
paid $2.60 and $2.40 and Ankles returned $3.60. 
</P>
</TEXT>
