<HEADLINE>
<P>
POTENTIALITY IS REALIZED IN LOUISIANA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOSSIER CITY, La. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Potentiality broke a close fifth out of the gate, then seized the lead after 
the first quarter en route to a 1 1/2-lengths victory in Friday's $100,000 
Island Whirl Handicap at Louisiana Downs. 
</P>
<P>
The 4-year-old colt, ridden by Earlie Fires, covered the seven furlongs in a 
near-record 1:22.2 and paid $22.40, $5.80 and $3.80 as a 10-1 outsider. 
</P>
<P>
Favored Black Tie Affair paid $2.60 and $2.40 for second, and Ankles returned 
$3.60 to show. 
</P>
<P>
Trained by Tom Proctor, Potentiality earned $60,000 for his fifth victory in 
seven starts and increased his career earnings to $113,766 for Glen Hill Farms. 
</P>
<P>
Friday's card launched a weekend of racing that peaks Sunday with the $1 
million Super Derby XI. 
</P>
<P>
Very Shortley took the lead shortly after the break and led the rest of the way 
to win the Devil's Bag Purse at Arlington International Racecourse in Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
Very Shortley, ridden by Kerwin Clark, finished the one mile in 1:37 over a 
sloppy track. 
</P>
<P>
Big Mukora rallied in the middle of the stretch to take second, 3 1/4 lengths 
behind. Big Mukora was another 7 1/4 lengths in front of third-place finisher 
Old Stories. 
</P>
<P>
Very Shortley, the favorite, returned $5.40, $3 and $2.20. Big Mukora paid 
$3.80 and $2.40 and Old Stories returned $2.20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
