<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CANADA; 
</P>
<P>
TROOPS IN EUROPE TO BE CUT BY 1,400 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Canada will reduce its troops in Europe by 1,400 next year, Defense Minister 
Bill McKnight announced in Ottawa. 
</P>
<P>
The cuts will be made at two Canadian bases in West Germany. "These are 
budget-driven reductions," McKnight said. He promised there would be no change 
in Canada's role in NATO as a result of the cuts. Canada has about 8,000 troops 
in West Germany. 
</P>
