<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MCKEON FIRED AS GENERAL MANAGER OF PADRES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jack McKeon was fired as general manager by the San Diego Padres on Friday, 
ending a decade-long stay with the club. 
</P>
<P>
The Padres' new ownership group, which bought the team from Joan Kroc in June, 
announced the firing after a day-long meeting. 
</P>
<P>
While stripped of his general manager's duties, McKeon, 59, apparently will 
allowed to stay with the club in some capacity. He is under contract through 
1991 at $400,000 per year. 
</P>
<P>
The Padres have already begun interviewing candidates for McKeon's job, and 
according to Times sources, have interviewed three candidates: Roger 
Jongewaard, Seattle Mariner vice president/scouting and player development; Dan 
Duquette, Montreal Expo assistant general manager, and Gordon Ash, Toronto Blue 
Jay assistant general manager. 
</P>
</TEXT>
