<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Security will be tight when the Asian Games open today in Beijing, but police 
have promised to keep a low profile. 
</P>
<P>
Just one day before the 16-day Games were scheduled to open, police searched 
pedestrians at random. Travelers in and out of the main train station had to 
pass through metal detectors as security officers X-rayed their luggage. 
</P>
<P>
Five-thousand athletes and 10,000 journalists and visitors are expected to 
attend the Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
