<P>
Al Davis and Pittsburgh Steeler Coach Chuck Noll were assistant coaches with 
the San Diego Chargers in 1960-62. Noll said Friday that although he and Davis 
remain friends, he hadn't spoken with the Raider owner recently. 
</P>
<P>
How does Noll remember the Raider-Steeler rivalry of the 1970s? "They were 
very, very physical," he said. "I don't expect this one (Sunday at the 
Coliseum) to be any less." 
</P>
<P>
Joe Walton, fired as coach of the New York Jets at the end of last season, was 
hired as the Steelers' offensive coordinator to revamp the offense, which 
ranked last in the NFL last season. But the Steelers have struggled this 
season, failing to score an offensive touchdown in two games. 
</P>
