<P>
PAULA SETTLE SLATKIN; PRODUCED, DIRECTED ABC'S 'EYE ON LA' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paula Settle Slatkin, former producer and director of ABC's "Eye on LA" and 
"Eye on Hollywood," has died. 
</P>
<P>
She was 33. 
</P>
<P>
She died Sunday at Cedars Sinai Hospital of cirrhosis of the liver. 
</P>
<P>
A Phi Beta Kappa graduate of Longwood College in Farmville, Va., Mrs. Slatkin 
was in charge of the television shows from 1981 to 1984. 
</P>
<P>
In 1985, she married Thomas Slatkin, one of the former owners of the Beverly 
Hills Hotel and Dana Point Resort. 
</P>
<P>
She was a member of the Directors Guild of America and worked for the Keagy 
Small Animal Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Besides her husband, she is survived by her mother, Jean Davis Settle, and a 
sister, Lynn McAdam. 
</P>
