<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAVY SAYS TWO COPTERS DIDN'T COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRIDGEPORT, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Strong winds forced two U.S. Navy helicopters to make rough landings on a 
forested slope in the Eastern Sierra Nevada, slightly injuring all nine people 
on board, officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
A Navy spokesman disputed initial reports that the two CH-46 Sea Knight 
helicopters had collided when they landed near Lobdell Lake in the Sweetwater 
Mountains about 6:30 p.m. Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
"It was not a collision, but a hard landing," said Navy spokesman Bob Howard. 
"They were flying in line, one forward and one aft, and a severe downdraft 
forced the one in back down first, and then the one in front was forced down." 
</P>
<P>
The incident remained under investigation by the Navy to determine the exact 
cause of the incident, Howard said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
