<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ARSENAL SEIZED FROM FARMHOUSE; 2 ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies who raided a secluded boarded-up 
Lancaster farmhouse seized an arsenal of guns, grenades, an anti-tank rocket 
launcher, cans of gunpowder -- and a live rattlesnake -- authorities said 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Two men were arrested at the farmhouse, which investigators said may have been 
used as a drug laboratory because a small amount of methamphetamine was found. 
</P>
<P>
The rattlesnake "scared the bejesus out of me," Sgt. Jim Brent said. The snake 
was seized by animal control officers. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies found a Dragon anti-tank rocket launcher but no rockets. Among the 
other items found were a replica of an M-60 machine gun and 20 small explosive 
devices, deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Sundahl and Edward Coleman, both 40 and of Lancaster, were arrested on 
suspicion of possession of explosive devices and were being held in lieu of 
$70,000 bail each at the sheriff's Antelope Valley station. 
</P>
