<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OXNARD; 
</P>
<P>
BUDGET HEAD TAKES MONO COUNTY POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oxnard Management and Budget Director Bill Mayer announced his resignation 
Friday to become head administrative officer for Mono County in Northern 
California. 
</P>
<P>
Mayer will leave Oxnard on Oct. 19 to replace Glenn Thompson, who recently 
resigned to become the city manager of Mammoth Lakes. 
</P>
<P>
Mayer, 46, has worked in Oxnard for 8 1/2 years. He has more than 20 years of 
experience in government, including working for county governments in San 
Diego, Ventura and Los Angeles counties. 
</P>
<P>
Mayer earns about $67,000 a year plus benefits in Oxnard, but he declined to 
discuss his new salary, saying his contract has not been approved by Mono 
County officials. 
</P>
<P>
Although the new position is expected to pay less, Mayer said he accepted the 
position as a career advancement. He said he will enjoy living in the rural 
setting. HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</TEXT>
