<P>
SANTA MARGARITA'S IRELAND GAINS RECORD 242 YARDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tailback Josh Ireland rushed for a school-record 242 yards in 15 carries and 
three touchdowns to lead Santa Margarita High School (3-0) to a 35-6 
nonconference victory over Banning (1-2) Friday night in Banning. 
</P>
<P>
Ireland, who also passed 26 yards to David Shearer for another Eagles' 
touchdown, set a school record when he ran 91 yards for his first touchdown on 
the initial play of Santa Margarita's second possession of the game. 
</P>
<P>
Shearer scored the Eagles' final touchdown when he recovered a fumble by 
Banning's punter and ran in from the seven yard line. 
</P>
