<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHNSON SCORES TWO TOUCHDOWNS, LA HABRA WINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LA HABRA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jason Johnson did it all for La Habra High School's football team during its 
26-0 rout of Los Altos Friday night at La Habra Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
Johnson, a junior running back, scored two touchdowns and gained 234 yards in 
30 carries. 
</P>
<P>
His longest run was 47 yards. His interception of Los Altos quarterback Mike 
Allen at midfield with 10 minutes 54 seconds left in the third period set up La 
Habra's first scoring drive that ended on a two-yard run by Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
Later in the third quarter, Sean Jackson blocked a punt by Ben Hernandez that 
was recovered by Mike Martin for La Habra (3-0) at the Los Altos 37. Five plays 
later, Johnson scored again from the two with 3:42 left. 
</P>
<P>
Then with 1:34 left in the third quarter, Matt Moreno returned a punt 75 yards 
for the Highlanders' final score. BOB BORSUM 
</P>
