PREP ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
VILLA PARK WINS IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kip Parsons scored six goals to lead Villa Park High School to a 14-8 victory 
over San Clemente in the Villa Park water polo tournament. 
</P>
<P>
San Clemente led, 3-2, in the first quarter, but by early in the fourth 
quarter, Villa Park (6-2) moved out to a 12-7 lead. Parsons scored three 
third-quarter goals in that run. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 13, Downey 8 -- John Lynn had eight goals to lead visiting Cypress 
(3-1). Bob Norum had two goals for Cypress. Robert Walshe had seven saves for 
Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
In nonleague girls' tennis: 
</P>
<P>
University 11, San Marcos 7 -- Jannette Fylpaa swept, 6-2, 6-0, 6-0, and 
Christina Pham swept, 6-1, 6-3, 6-2, to lead host University (3-3). 
</P>
