<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PACIFICA TAKES TO THE AIR, SENDS GLENN REELING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN HILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chris Castellano threw two second-quarter touchdown passes to lead Pacifica 
High School to a 14-0 victory over Glenn High on Friday in a nonleague game in 
front of 500 at La Mirada High School. 
</P>
<P>
Castellano was 12 for 28 for 137 yards with no interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
His first touchdown was a nine-yarder to Jim Lochner with 10 minutes 17 seconds 
left in the second quarter. Pacifica (2-1) started the short scoring drive at 
the Glenn 15 because Glenn punter Jerry Jornadal touched his knee to the ground 
going for a low snap. 
</P>
<P>
The second scoring pass came on Pacifica's next possession. Castellano 
completed a 14-yarder to Eric Stevens. The play capped a 66-yard, eight-play 
drive. Dave Anderson kicked both extra points. 
</P>
<P>
Pacifica's defense was impressive as well. The Mariners held Glenn (2-1) to 17 
yards in the first half and 98 overall. KEN HILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
