<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEN HALL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Laguna Beach 16, Pius X 0 -- Laguna Beach High School turned two Pius X 
turnovers into touchdowns and won its first game of the season, 16-0, Friday 
night at Guyer Field. 
</P>
<P>
The first touchdown came in the first quarter after senior linebacker Sean 
Sauers recovered a fumble on the Pius X 24-yard line. 
</P>
<P>
Two plays later, receiver Mike Dennis tipped senior quarterback Morgan 
Lanchantin's 18-yard pass into the hands of Matt Guss in the end zone for the 
Laguna Beach touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
The final Artist touchdown came after senior linebacker J.T. Klingenmeier 
picked off his second pass of the night at the Pius X 19-yard line. Six plays 
later, Lanchantin sneaked in for the touchdown from one yard out with 4:15 left 
in the game. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach (1-2) also scored on a 25-yard field goal by Eric Fegraus in the 
third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Pius X (0-3) was led by running back Devon English, who ran for 76 yards in 18 
carries. LEN HALL 
</P>
</TEXT>
