<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP FOOTBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHUCK BOCK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Servite 23, Alemany 15 -- Friar running back Mike Wallock bulled his way for 
149 yards and two touchdowns in 22 carries to lead Servite to a 23-15 victory 
over Alemany at Cerritos College Friday. 
</P>
<P>
The senior running back scored on runs from two yards and one yard out. 
</P>
<P>
With the game tied 7-7, Servite (2-1) scored nine points in a three-minute span 
in the third quarter. A 54-yard punt return by Mike Hill set up Wallock's 
one-yard go-ahead touchdown, and an interception by Robert Choi set up a field 
goal by Josh Nelson. 
</P>
<P>
Servite took a 23-7 lead on running back Chandler Robbins' 16-yard run with two 
minutes gone in the fourth quarter to cap a seven-play, 75-yard drive. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany (1-1) had taken a 7-0 lead on a 38-yard interception return by Wrangell 
Melendres with 10:44 left in the first quarter, but didn't score again until 
Tom Engler caught a four-yard touchdown pass from Adam Romandi with 3:34 left 
in the game. CHUCK BOCK 
</P>
</TEXT>
