<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CHAPMAN GAINS ITS FIRST SOCCER VICTORY OF THE SEASON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Voss and Cody Starrett scored to give the Chapman men's soccer team a 2-0 
victory over La Verne in a nonconference men's soccer match at Chapman Friday. 
It was Chapman's first victory of the season. 
</P>
<P>
Voss scored a goal 15 minutes into the first half and Starrett followed with a 
score 18 minutes later to pace Chapman (1-3-1). 
</P>
<P>
Goalie John Kinley had four saves for his first shutout of the season. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 5, Loyola Marymount 1 -- Kevin Smith scored two goals to pace UC 
Irvine (3-5-1) in a match at Loyola. Erik Nasarenko, John O'Brien and Anthony 
Russomanno also scored for Irvine, which led, 3-0, at halftime. Loyola's score 
was by Eric Hill. Irvine goalie Mike Gartlan had six saves. Mike Luken had nine 
saves for Loyola (2-3). 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Northridge 2, Southern California College 1 -- Danny Daniels scored 
once in each half to give host Cal State Northridge (3-4-1) a 2-0 lead. 
Southern California College's Bijan Chavoshan scored to cut the lead to one. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Nevada Las Vegas 2, Cal State Fullerton 1 -- In the conference opener Friday, 
visiting Cal State Fullerton (1-3-2, 0-1) took a 1-0 lead on forward Raul 
Haro's first-half goal. UNLV (4-1-2, 1-0) tied the score early in the second 
half on a goal by Doug Borgel, and won it with a goal late in the second half. 
Goalies Jay Nettekoven of Cal State Fullerton and Doug Schell of UNLV each had 
five saves. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West Conference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
UC Santa Barbara d. UC Irvine, 15-5, 15-9, 15-8 -- Kristie Ryan had seven kills 
and 13 digs to lead UC Santa Barbara (12-1, 1-0) in the conference-opening 
match for both schools at Irvine. For Irvine (4-6, 0-1), Kim Collins had 10 
kills and 14 digs. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Baptist d. Southern California College, 15-11, 15-6, 8-15, 15-12 -- Leslie 
Lastrapes had 13 kills and 10 blocks for host SCC. Kathy Westfall also had 16 
assists for SCC (12-10). 
</P>
<P>
In Golden State Athletic Assn. women's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Point Loma 3, Christ College Irvine 2 -- Miriam Paulus of Christ College Irvine 
had 17 kills but Christ College Irvine lost to Point Loma, 15-13, 7-15, 14-16, 
15-8, 15-9. 
</P>
