<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; 
</P>
<P>
DEPUTIES ARREST HIT-RUN SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 33-year-old Dana Point man was arrested Friday at a San Bernardino County 
home on suspicion of felony hit-and-run, according to sheriff's officials. 
</P>
<P>
Timothy William Underwood, who was described as a self-employed artist, was 
arrested about 4:45 a.m. after his blue Honda was traced to a home in Grand 
Terrace, said Lt. Richard J. Olson of the Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Underwood is scheduled to be arraigned Monday, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Underwood is suspected of running into Charlotte Ann Englis, 66, of Laguna 
Beach while she was riding her bicycle about 3:45 p.m. Aug. 31 near the 
intersection of Del Obispo Street and Windjammer Drive in San Juan Capistrano. 
According to witnesses, Underwood stopped momentarily to ask the victim if she 
was hurt and then left the scene, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
A license plate fell off Underwood's 1982 Honda during the accident, enabling 
deputies to trace the vehicle to a Dana Point residence and then to Grand 
Terrace, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Englis suffered a concussion, a broken right ankle and abrasions in the 
accident, Olson said. 
</P>
<P>
Bail for Underwood was set at $10,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
